    %h2.block-title Greenwire grid
    %p
      :markdown
        Greenwire uses the [SingularityGS](https://github.com/at-import/Singularity) grid framework. We have a default of 12 columns, which are fluid and gutters are `14px` by default.

        Starting mobile first we have no columns. Screens wider than `900px` get one of the following layouts:

        ###1. 50/50 Layout
        This layout has two equal columns which will both be `480px` maximum.

    .l-two-column.clearfix
      .l-main-column
        %div{:style => "background:grey; min-height:100px;padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; color: #FFF;"} left column
      .l-sidebar.sidebar
        .block{:style => "background:grey; min-height:100px;padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; color: #FFF;"} right column
    %p
      :markdown
        ###2. Two-third / One-third Layout
        This layout has one main column and one sidebar column. The main column has a maximum width of `640px` (2/3 of 960) and a padding on the right `7px`. The content can therefore be stretched at a maximum of `633px`.

        The sidebar can stretch to a maximum of `320px` (1/3 of 960) and has a padding on the left of `7px`. The content in the sidebar can therefor stretch to a maximum of `313px`. Most content in the sidbar is stored in [blocks](/components/blocks.html). These block have a side padding of `14px` each. When designing for the largest screens, you will have `285px` available for content in this layout.

    .l-has-sidebar.clearfix
      .l-main-column#current
        .block{:style => "background:grey; min-height:100px;padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; color: #FFF;"} left column
      .l-sidebar.sidebar
        .block{:style => "background:grey; min-height:100px;padding: 15px; border-radius: 4px; color: #FFF;"} right column
